Vanishing Cycles of Irregular D-Modules
snippet.description: Considering a holonomic -module and a hypersurface, we define a finite family of -modules on the hypersurface which we call modules of vanishing cycles. The first one had been previously defined and corresponds to formal solutions. The last one corresponds, via Riemann-Hilbert, to the geometric vanishing cycles of Grothendieck-Deligne.
